    "According to the report of 41, the time spent on research and analyzing diagnostic data will decrease when quantum computing is integrated with healthcare systems.",
    "With this motivation, the paper aims to implement Quantum Enhanced Machine Learning approaches for diagnosing heart diseases and it yields a remarkable accuracy rate and computation time shown in \"Results and discussions\" by simply replacing classical probability theory with quantum probability theory and it makes use of superposition state that provides a higher degree of freedom in decision making.",
    "It describes the datasets that have been used to implement QuEML (Quantum Enhanced Machine Learning) Framework for heart disease diagnosis.",
    "The Heart Disease Dataset (HDD) is taken from the Kaggle repository and it is a comprehensive dataset of 1190 instances which is a combination of five different datasets listed in Table 2 and the combination is based on 11 common features with one target variable listed in Table 3.",
